{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-lesson-template-js","path":"/hooking-up-state","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Alright, so we have Redux connected to React in spirit, but the component isn't really using anything here.</p>\n<p>We're going to get more into selectors in a bit, but‚Äîat a high level‚Äîthey do what they say they do on the tin: they select pieces from our state tree.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> useSelector <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react-redux'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">/* üåù */</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">Counter</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> incident <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Incident'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> count <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">useSelector</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">state</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> state<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>count<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token comment\">/* üåù */</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// ‚Ä¶</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> Counter<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>It's zero by default in our state, so our UI hasn't changed much. But, we <em>could</em> trigger this from the developer tools if we wanted. Let's dispatch the following action.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  type<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'INCREMENT'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>We can see the count increment, which is good. We can also see the actions logged into the tools. We can even roll back the state if want. (<strong>Hint</strong>: The Redux Developer Tools are using the enhancer to add this functionality to our store. We'll see how to do something similar later.)</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/hooking-up-state","title":"Hooking Up State","order":"3D","section":"Hooking It Up With React","description":"Getting started and an introduction to TypeScript && React Workshop"}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"8A","path":"/create-async-thunk","title":"Creating Async Thunks in Redux Toolkit"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"8B","path":"/pulling-it-all-together","title":"Pulling It Together in React Toolkit"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"2G","path":"/middleware-and-enhancers","title":"Middleware and Enhancers"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"2E","path":"/bind-action-creators","title"